## Pattern D — Commander-specific knowledge (e.g. Aloy Discover)

When a validated guide exists under `docs/commander-guides/`:

1. Read MCP resource or file **before** building (trigger rules, scoring ceiling, anti-patterns).
2. Use **`preferredStrategy`** from the guide (Aloy Discover → `artifacts`).
3. Prefer manual targeted fixes over blind **`optimize_deck`** when the guide warns about false off-theme cuts.
4. Compare against **`data/reference-decks/`** when validating swaps.

Example: Aloy Discover → `.cursor/rules/aloy-discover-deck.mdc`, `docs/commander-guides/aloy-discover.md`.

## Anti-patterns

- Building before user confirms synergy slug.
- Using `proliferate` or other free text instead of EDHREC slugs (use `counters` for +1/+1).
- Skipping `optimize_deck` when many categories are `below`.
- Applying swaps when `evaluate_card_swap` returns `skip`.
- Blind **`optimize_deck`** on commander-specific lists when a guide warns it cuts engine pieces (see Aloy Discover).
- Rejecting **fast mana** as “illegal for Bracket 3” — fast mana is allowed; some pieces are Game Changers (`docs/bracket3-official-rules.md`).
